div1.p: Territory of Washington County of Spokane} ss.
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, Spo- kane County, in said Territory
To the Sheriff of Spokane County, Greeting:

In the name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon Eli Wanck James Greivston Aaron Thompson Mel Call to be and appear before the District Court aforesaid at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the instantes day of April A.D. 1885, at o'clock M., to there give evi- dence in the above entitled cause on the part of said Defendant.

WITNESS the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed, this 29 day of April A.D. 1885 Kate W. Feuerbach Clerk. By R. Strobach Deputy.
Territory of Washington, County of Spokane }ss.

I hereby certify that I served the within subpoena on the within named witness by reading the same to them in said county, on this 29 day of April A.D. 1885 E.F. Whittier Sheriff. By H.B. Mason Deputy.
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, in said Territory.
Territory PLAINTIFF. vs. Coyle DEFENDANT. Returned and filed this 30 day of April A.D. 1885 Kate W. Feuerbach Clerk. By R. Strobach Deputy.
SHERIFF'S FEES Serving 4 names at 40 1.60 Mileage 42 miles at 10 4.20 Total, ----$5.80 E.F. Whittier Sheriff By H.B. Mason Deputy
